<br>
Does Dire Charm drain your mana pool, lose all your mana regen buffs, take a reagant? NO.<br>
<br>
Does Life Burn or Mana Burn cause KEI etc.. to drop. No. Does it take a reagant. NO.<br>
<br>
Neither should ours if we get a &quot;FIX&quot;, sure if it needs to take mana as does Life/Mana burn, so let it be an all at once drain. It takes the mana, but your buggs stay in place, and PLEASE STOP asking for expensive reagants to be used.<br>
<br>
The recast time should be EXACTLY the same as Manaburn, not 1 second more or less, as it is our form of manaburn.<br>
<br>
Please at times I feel we are our own worse enemy when it comes to asking that a &quot;FIX&quot; to a real problem is needed to be implimented.<br>
<br>
I know why, because you think without that it won't be done, so hence the inbuilt nurf. All clarity type buffs drop, a very expernsive and rare gem required, or 2. A refresh timer way longer than the other 3 INT casters refresh timers.. etc..<br>
<br>
I like Silverblades idea, of a mean a$$ pet, but without the gem cost, and the usual refresh timer of manaburn.<br>
<br>
Not over powered, in my book. I would agree though like any pet, you have to &quot;lose&quot; the current pet to get the new one, or if it is a buff to an existing pet, than you need one up. Click the icon and WHAM your pet is transformed for a set duration (more than 36 seconds), and when the timer runs out, it reverts back to the pet it was.<br>
