<br>
Magicians should never, in any way, get a persistant pet better than the best that enchanters can dire charm.<br>
<br>
Why? Because dire charm has limitations that a persistant pet does not. Dire charm and pets are close enough to be compared. It is clear that dire charm is more limited than pets are, therefore it should be more powerful when it can be used.<br>
<br>
Now, I think frenzied burnout is the right way to go for the uber mage AA. Obviously, it's crap right now if it doesn't significantly increase the damage output.<br>
<br>
Also, they need to add ancient pet spells. Ancient spells are supposed to give casters power in compare to what melees get by looting primal velium warswords and fists of lightning.<br>
<br>
There should be 4 level 60 pet summons. Summon Ancient Elemental: Fire/Air/Earth/Water. Or maybe for flavor, Smoke/Sand/Mud/Mist. They should be better than the epic pet, have abilities of the same line as the normal elementals. Earth one should do decent melee damage, have good AC, about 5-6k hp, cast dooming darkness on opponents, and HT when it gets to 5% health. Etc. <p><center>
