<br>
Say AA pet has 200 DPS.<br>
Manaburn does between 8k and 10k, depending on gear and non Crit.<br>
8000 to 10,000/200 = 40 to 50 second pet.<br>
<br>
This would be a pet that has the attack, HP and AC of a 60 warrior in above average gear, with average resists.<br>
<br>
<br>
My idea of it doing a steady mana drain with no mana Regen spells was to allow more functionality and still keep it fair.  Uber mages with more mana will get more time out of thier pet, as will mages supported by bards, healers, etc,  Just as Wizards with Uber Gear get better Manaburns due to higher mana.<br>
<br>
It would also allow more flexability, allowing you higher burst DPS by also casting while the pet is doing damage, or sitting and medding for faster Regen, and allowing you to kill pet at will by clicking off the Icon to get rid of it if it becomes a liability for any reason.<br>
<br>
Getting rid of mana buffs was to keep it from:<br>
A&gt;needing HUGE manadrain to make up for having those buffs at all times.<br>
B&gt;being a permanant pet due to excessive mana regen.<br>
<br>
It was not intended to be a Nurf at all, just a really cool ability. <p><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/atl/d/a/dastorys/Pictures/Necsig.jpg>

