<br>
1. Increase haste cap to 100%<br>
2. Increase caps on all stats to 255 just like PCs. Right now there is a perceived ceiling on these (i.e. avatar testing on pets seem to indicate very little change in damage).<br>
<br>
                ----Once those are done----<br>
<br>
*AA skill #1: Frenzied BO: +100 to all stats/+200 to atk/+100 to AC/+100 to haste/increase max damage by 5.  Lasts until mob dies or pet is killed. Reusable every 72 min.<br>
<br>
*AA skill #2: Sumpreme Focus: Turns the pet into the perfect essence of its element, increasing its level by 2 (doesn't stack with focus elemental items); its innate procs to lures; or in the case of fire pet allowing it the ability to Innately crit like a wizard of its level and cast Thunderstrike/inferno shock/ice strike(level 29 &amp; 34 spells). Drains mage of all mana(have to be full mana to initiate power)--pet lasts until killed or mage zones.  Reusable every 72 min.<br>
<br>
The first skill is for raids against boss mob targets.  The second skill is our answer to dire charm (i.e. a heightened pet that last just like DC--DC pet would still be more damaging IMO, but this would be a skill I would invest in).<br>
<br>
As far as pets that can take an AoE attack.  Well if a pet can demonstrate its power to the raid force then it will garner the respect of buffs just like a DC pet.  Epic pet with Frenzied BO as stated above would do substantial damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uduolos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Duolos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(6/17/02 2:54:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .....</span><hr size=1> /rant on<br>
